    <div id="possiblylost-notes" type="gl-notes">
        <head>Notes</head>
        <list type="ordered">
            <item>The first example indicates the <hi rend="strong">possible</hi> loss of exactly three characters (the alternative possibility is that there was originally a vacat in this space.</item>
            <item>The second example indicates the <hi rend="strong">possible</hi> loss of approximately three characters.</item>
            <item>The third example indicates the <hi rend="strong">possible</hi> loss of exactly 10 characters.</item>
            <item>The fourth example indicates the <hi rend="strong">possible</hi> loss of approximately 10 characters.</item>
            <item>The fifth example indicates the <hi rend="strong">possible</hi> loss of text in a horizontal span of 4.2cm.</item>
            <item>The sixth example indicates the <hi rend="strong">possible</hi> loss of exactly one line of text.</item>
            <item>The seventh example indicates the <hi rend="strong">possible</hi> loss of one or more lines of text.</item>
            <item>For cases wherein the editor is certain that text has been lost and the only ambiguity, if any, pertains to the number of characters thus lost, see <xref href="lostcertain.xml">Letters completely lost (extent certain or not certain)</xref>.</item>
        </list>
